repsilon>0$ such that for any $k\\in\\mathbb{N}$, we have\n$\\lim\\limits_{n\\to\\infty}\\mathbb{P}\\Big\\{\\frac{|\\lambda_{|k|}(A_n)|}{2\\sqrt{n\np_n}}>1+\\varepsilon\\Big\\}=1$.\n  On a conceptual level, our result highlights similarities in appearance of\noutliers in spectrum of sparse matrices and the so-called BBP phase transition\nphenomenon in deformed Wigner matrices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Apr 2019 21:03:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 22 Apr 2019 10:46:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 28 Apr 2019 03:18:45 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 23 May 2019 11:07:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-24"}
